snippet.textDisplay:
It is irrefutable that Sufi culture is one of the greatest and glorious known culture in the world. Originally, the song was written by Nizam Auliya's most beloved disciple, Amir Khusro, for his equally beloved guru, peer, Nizam Auliya. It is also well known from history that Khusrau gave up his life the very next day after the death of his Nizam. He was cremated at the same place located in Delhi's Nizamuddin Dargah.

Apart from history, these musical instruments and the wonderful voice of Ustad Rahat Fateh Ali are equally praiseworthy..
And some will definitely get goosebumps  in 3:05 and 8:18 .
